{"parentUuid":"07fcceeb-7072-4bc3-a798-a64c64c35841","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"a7ee3ee9393a65a0e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015p91B1Xprnrykkm6qUPJX7","type":"tool_result","content":"<persisted-output>\nOutput too large (39.3KB). Full output saved to: C:\\Users\\brett\\.claude\\projects\\c--Users-brett-OneDrive-Documents-GitHub-meterly-pipeline-test\\cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f\\tool-results\\blarvz8eq.txt\n\nPreview (first 2KB):\ndiff --git a/src/api/README.md b/src/api/README.md\nindex d49e044..d5ece81 100644\n--- a/src/api/README.md\n+++ b/src/api/README.md\n@@ -11,14 +11,14 @@ HTTP API layer: FastAPI route handlers, request/response schemas (Pydantic v2),\n | `routes/events.py` | `POST /v1/events` handler; calls `events_service.create_event`. |\n | `routes/usage.py` | `GET /v1/usage` handler; calls `usage_service.get_usage`. |\n | `routes/usage_export.py` | `GET /v1/usage/export` handler; two-phase pre-flight row-cap check (`usage_export_service.prepare_export`) then a `StreamingResponse` body (`usage_export_service.stream_export_csv`). Kept in its own module (not added to `usage.py`) so `GET /v1/usage`'s code path stays untouched. Declares explicit `responses=` OpenAPI metadata (200 `text/csv`, 422) since a `StreamingResponse` has no `response_model` to introspect. |\n-| `routes/quotas.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` handler; composes auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> an `admin`-scope gate (403 `forbidden` otherwise) -> `quota_service.upsert_tenant_quota`. |\n+| `routes/quotas.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas`, `GET /v1/quotas`, and `DELETE /v1/quotas` handlers, all composing the shared `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency (auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> an `admin`-scope gate, 403 `forbidden` otherwise). `PUT` calls `quota_service.upsert_tenant_quota`; `GET` (`list_quotas_endpoint`) calls `quota_service.list_tenant_quotas` and returns `list[QuotaResponse]`; `DELETE` (`delete_quota